# 🧮 Day 10 - Calculator

This is a basic calculator app built with Python, created for Day 10 of the **100 Days of Code** challenge.

It supports addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division. Users can perform continuous calculations using the result of the previous operation.

## 🚀 Features

- Basic arithmetic operations: add, subtract, multiply, divide
- Continuous calculation support
- Input validation and error handling
- Simple, console-based interface

## 🛠️ Built With

- Python 3

## 🧠 What I Practiced

- Functions and return values
- Control flow with `while` loops
- Dictionary-based operation handling
- Clearing the console for better UX

---

Part of the [100 Days of Code](https://github.com/Synel96/100-Days-Of-Code) journey.
